{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place biscuits into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>, until they resemble breadcrumbs. Transfer into a sealable container and set aside until ready to use.","Place cocoa powder, white sugar and cornflour into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add eggs and milk and cook <nobr>7 min\/90°C\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Divide evenly between 12 mini terracotta flower pots and place into refrigerator until completely cool (approx. 20 minutes). Do not clean mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream, yoghurt and caster sugar into mixing bowl and whip <nobr>20-40 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr> or until just thick. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk. <\/strong> ","Remove chocolate custard cups from refrigerator and top evenly with yoghurt mixture. Cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator for 1 hour or overnight to cool and set. Top with reserved biscuit crumbs and decorate with lollies or other edible decorations just before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["130 - 150 g plain chocolate biscuits","20 g cocoa powder","60 g white sugar","30 g cornflour","2 eggs","500 g full cream milk","200 g pouring (whipping) cream","200 g vanilla yoghurt","40 g caster sugar, to taste","lollies of choice or other edible decorations (see Tip)"]}],"id":"r141119","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-kLjEpW1uIpo\/XZWe_h8kaOI\/AAAAAAAAe9E\/cg_h7TUN13UQ006YHs7KoJnfE6hMU7a5QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_loi-b51vNFsRzHYW.png","title":"Dirt puddings","publishedAt":"2017-10-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5.8 g","fat":"11.4 g","uom":"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"36.2 g","calories":"1114 kJ \/ 265 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sealable container, 12 mini terracotta flower pots, plastic wrap, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Use any kind of edible decorations to finish off your dirt puddings to suit the theme of your party (e.g. flowers, ladybirds, bugs and boulders)."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 30m","12 portions"]}